# Deep Architecture Audit

This document tracks our systematic, batch-by-batch deep audit of the Sehri Finder application.

## Batch 1 Complete: Global Entry, Routing & Context

### Scope Inspected
- `src/index.tsx` (Entry point)
- `src/App.tsx` (Routing & Layout)
- `src/context/LanguageContext.tsx` (Localization)

### Findings & Risks

#### 1. CRITICAL: Missing Suspense Boundary (App.tsx)
**Smell/Bug**: [AppPage](file:///c:/Users/HP/Downloads/sehri/pages/AppPage.tsx#17-282), [SubmitPage](file:///c:/Users/HP/Downloads/sehri/pages/SubmitPage.tsx#6-20), and Admin pages are dynamically imported via `React.lazy()`. However, the `<Routes>` tree in [App.tsx](file:///c:/Users/HP/Downloads/sehri/App.tsx) is **not wrapped in a `<Suspense>` boundary**. 
**Risk**: If a user navigates from the Landing Page to `/find` or `/submit`, React will throw an uncaught error because the lazy component hasn't downloaded yet and there is no fallback UI provided.

#### 2. UX Bug: Rogue Keyboard Shortcut (App.tsx)
**Smell/Bug**: The `Shift + A` global event listener for the Admin panel does not check `event.target`.
**Risk**: If a user holds `Shift` to type a capital 'A' inside the Search Bar or a Form Input, they will be instantly redirected to the login page, destroying their session/input data.

#### 3. Bug: Initial RTL Hydration Failure (LanguageContext.tsx)
**Smell/Bug**: When reading the user's saved language from `localStorage` on initial load (inside `useEffect`), it updates the React state but *forgets* to sync `document.documentElement.dir` to `rtl`. 
**Risk**: If an Urdu user refreshes the page, the text will translate, but the physical DOM layout will revert to Left-To-Right until they manually toggle the language again.

### Incremental Fix Plan (Batch 1)
- [ ] Add `<Suspense fallback={<GlobalLoader/>}>` inside [App.tsx](file:///c:/Users/HP/Downloads/sehri/App.tsx).
- [ ] Add `tagName` checks to the `Shift+A` listener to ignore `INPUT` and `TEXTAREA`.
- [ ] Move the `dir` and `lang` DOM mutation into a synchronized effect inside [LanguageContext](file:///c:/Users/HP/Downloads/sehri/context/LanguageContext.tsx#5-11).

