## Batch 5 Complete: Admin & Submission Flows

### Scope Inspected
- `src/pages/AdminDashboardPage.tsx`
- `src/components/admin/AdminDashboard.tsx`
- `src/components/SubmitSpot.tsx`
- `src/components/admin/ApprovalModal.tsx`

### Findings & Risks

#### 1. SECURITY VULNERABILITY: Missing Route Guards ([AdminDashboardPage.tsx](file:///c:/Users/HP/Downloads/sehri/pages/AdminDashboardPage.tsx))
**Smell/Bug**: The [AdminDashboardPage](file:///c:/Users/HP/Downloads/sehri/pages/AdminDashboardPage.tsx#5-16) simply renders `<AdminDashboard />` without verifying if a Supabase authentication session exists on mount.
**Risk**: Anyone who navigates directly to `/admin/dashboard` will load the full React admin UI. While Supabase RLS (Row Level Security) might block the actual data fetching, the UI will still mount, show errors, and expose the internal layout.
**Fix**: Add an `AuthContext` or a simple `useEffect` in the page wrapper to call `supabase.auth.getSession()`. If no session, `navigate('/admin')`.

#### 2. ARCHITECTURE BUG: No Pagination Limits Editing ([AdminDashboard.tsx](file:///c:/Users/HP/Downloads/sehri/components/admin/AdminDashboard.tsx))
**Smell/Bug**: [fetchLiveSpots()](file:///c:/Users/HP/Downloads/sehri/components/admin/AdminDashboard.tsx#74-98) uses `.limit(100)`. There is no "Load More" button or pagination.
**Risk**: With over 260+ spots already seeded, Admins can never see, select, or edit spots past the first 100 unless they luckily search for the exact name.
**Fix**: Change the UI to fetch more as the user scrolls, or increase the limit to 1000 for the admin view, or add simple `offset` pagination.

#### 3. UX/SCHEMA FLAW: Submission Data Incompleteness ([SubmitSpot.tsx](file:///c:/Users/HP/Downloads/sehri/components/SubmitSpot.tsx) vs [ListingCard.tsx](file:///c:/Users/HP/Downloads/sehri/components/ListingCard.tsx))
**Smell/Bug**: The [SubmitSpot](file:///c:/Users/HP/Downloads/sehri/components/SubmitSpot.tsx#24-263) public form only asks for basic info (Name, City, Timing). However, [ApprovalModal](file:///c:/Users/HP/Downloads/sehri/components/admin/ApprovalModal.tsx#13-310) and the actual [SehriSpot](file:///c:/Users/HP/Downloads/sehri/types.ts#42-100) UI rely heavily on arrays like `features[]` (e.g. DeliveryAvailable, LadiesFriendly) and `phones[]` to render rich cards.
**Risk**: When users submit spots, the Admin has to manually guess or call the user to find out if there is a Women's section or Delivery. As a result, community-submitted spots look very empty on the frontend compared to the initial seeded data.
**Fix**: Add checkboxes in [SubmitSpot.tsx](file:///c:/Users/HP/Downloads/sehri/components/SubmitSpot.tsx) for core features (`Delivery`, `Dine-In`, `Women's Section`) and an input for `Phone Number`.

### Incremental Fix Plan (Batch 5)
- [ ] Add a top-level route guard to [AdminDashboardPage.tsx](file:///c:/Users/HP/Downloads/sehri/pages/AdminDashboardPage.tsx).
- [ ] Increase live spot limit or add basic pagination in [AdminDashboard.tsx](file:///c:/Users/HP/Downloads/sehri/components/admin/AdminDashboard.tsx).
- [ ] Enhance public [SubmitSpot.tsx](file:///c:/Users/HP/Downloads/sehri/components/SubmitSpot.tsx) to collect Phone and basic Features.

