## Batch 6 Complete: Performance, PWA & Configuration

### Scope Inspected
- [vite.config.ts](file:///c:/Users/HP/Downloads/sehri/vite.config.ts) (Build Strategy)
- [index.html](file:///c:/Users/HP/Downloads/sehri/index.html) (Bootstrap & Fonts)
- [index.css](file:///c:/Users/HP/Downloads/sehri/index.css) (Style Bloat)
- `src/components/ErrorBoundary.tsx`
- `src/components/ReloadPrompt.tsx`

### Findings & Risks

#### 1. CRITICAL PERFORMANCE: Extreme Font Overload ([index.html](file:///c:/Users/HP/Downloads/sehri/index.html))
**Smell/Bug**: The application is currently loading **9 separate Google Font families** (Outfit, Cormorant Garamond, Cinzel, Great Vibes, Amiri, Reem Kufi, Playfair Display, Lora, Source Serif 4, Montserrat).
**Risk**: Every font family requires a high-priority network request. Loading 9 different fonts (and their weights) will destroy the Performance score on mobile devices, causing high Cumulative Layout Shift (CLS) and blocking the Largest Contentful Paint (LCP) for several seconds. 
**Fix**: Consolidate to exactly **3 brand fonts** (e.g., Reem Kufi for Arabic/Headings, Outfit for Sans, and Playfair for Serif). Use standard system fallbacks for the rest.

#### 2. ARCHITECTURE SMELL: Environment-Specific build paths ([vite.config.ts](file:///c:/Users/HP/Downloads/sehri/vite.config.ts))
**Smell/Bug**: The `prerender` plugin has a hardcoded `executablePath` pointing to a local Windows C: drive path for Chrome.
**Risk**: The build will immediately fail on Vercel, GitHub Actions, or any other developer's machine that isn't yours.
**Fix**: Remove the hardcoded path; `puppeteer` should find the browser automatically or we should use an environment variable.

#### 3. BUILD OPTIMIZATION: Heavy Dependency Chunking ([vite.config.ts](file:///c:/Users/HP/Downloads/sehri/vite.config.ts))
**Smell/Bug**: Only `react` and `lucide` are split into manual chunks.
**Risk**: `framer-motion` and `leaflet` are both ~100kb+ and are likely being bundled into the main `index.js`, making the initial load unnecessarily heavy.
**Fix**: Create dedicated chunks for `vendor-framer` and `vendor-maps`.

### Incremental Fix Plan (Batch 6)
- [ ] Reduce Google Fonts to the critical minimum in [index.html](file:///c:/Users/HP/Downloads/sehri/index.html).
- [ ] Remove hardcoded Windows paths from [vite.config.ts](file:///c:/Users/HP/Downloads/sehri/vite.config.ts).
- [ ] Refine Rollup manual chunks for heavy dependencies.

