## 🚀 Execution Strategy: Phase 6 Roadmap

The Deep Audit is complete. We will now move into **Execution Mode** to apply these surgical fixes. We will proceed by batch to ensure the app remains stable and testable.

### 🛡️ The "Safety Net" Strategy (Zero Regression Framework)

To guarantee that these deep architectural fixes do not break the existing UI or user flows, I will enforce the following strict protocols during execution:

1. **Atomic, Isolated Changes (One File at a Time)**
   We will not do a "big bang" rewrite. Each batch will be executed individually. For example, when fixing the [useSpotFilter](file:///c:/Users/HP/Downloads/sehri/hooks/useSpotFilter.ts#29-127) hook, we will *only* touch that hook and verify it before moving to the [AdminDashboard](file:///c:/Users/HP/Downloads/sehri/components/admin/AdminDashboard.tsx#42-412).
2. **Pre-Flight Dependency Mapping**
   Before changing the signature of any exported Context, Hook, or Utility (like [formatTiming](file:///c:/Users/HP/Downloads/sehri/utils/transformers.ts#18-31) or [SehriContext](file:///c:/Users/HP/Downloads/sehri/context/SehriContext.tsx#10-33)), I will run a global `grep_search` to find *every single component* that consumes it. I will update the providers and consumers in the exact same step.
3. **TypeScript Compilation as a Firewall**
   After every logical batch of changes, I will run the TypeScript compiler (`npx tsc --noEmit` or equivalent build checks). If the types mismatch (e.g., if a component tries to read `spot.distance` instead of dynamically computing it), the compiler will catch it before the browser does.
4. **Vite Build Verification**
   Since Phase 4 introduced SSG Prerendering, the build process is highly sensitive to DOM manipulations (like the Portals bug). After completing the high-risk batches, I will run a dry-run `npm run build` to ensure the Node SSR engine does not crash and the Vite bundle successfully compiles.
5. **No Visual Destructivism**
   The CSS and UI components (like [FilterBar.tsx](file:///c:/Users/HP/Downloads/sehri/components/FilterBar.tsx) and [ListingCard.tsx](file:///c:/Users/HP/Downloads/sehri/components/ListingCard.tsx)) will have their *prop-drilling* removed, but the underlying Tailwind classes and JSX layout will remain 100% untouched.

### Execution Sequence:
1. **Critical High-Impact**: Fonts (Batch 6), Suspense (Batch 1), JSONB Schema (Batch 4).
2. **Security & State**: Auth Guards (Batch 5), Context Fetching (Batch 2).
3. **Performance & UX**: Debouncing (Batch 3), O(1) Sets (Batch 2), Pagination (Batch 5).
4. **Cleanup**: Prop Drilling (Batch 3), Hardcoded IDs (Batch 4).

