## Batch 3 Complete: Maps, UI Components, and Layout Shifts

### Scope Inspected
- `src/components/MapView.tsx` (Leaflet Map)
- `src/components/Hero.tsx` (Search & Parallax)
- `src/components/FilterBar.tsx` (Complex State UI)
- `src/pages/AppPage.tsx` (Parent Mount)

### Findings & Risks

#### 1. Performance/UX Bug: Missing Search Input Debounce (Hero.tsx)
**Smell/Bug**: The [Hero](file:///c:/Users/HP/Downloads/sehri/components/Hero.tsx#39-205) search input triggers `onSearch(e.target.value)` on every single keystroke. This instantly updates [SehriContext](file:///c:/Users/HP/Downloads/sehri/context/SehriContext.tsx#10-33) and forces the massive [useSpotFilter](file:///c:/Users/HP/Downloads/sehri/hooks/useSpotFilter.ts#29-127) algorithm to recalculate the entire database on every letter typed.
**Risk**: On lower-end mobile devices, typing "Biryani" will freeze the UI thread 7 times context-switching between rendering the input and filtering the array. 
**Fix**: Implement `useDeferredValue` (React 18) or a standard 300ms debounce timeout on the local search state before pushing to context.

#### 2. Architecture Smell: Unnecessary Prop Drilling (FilterBar.tsx)
**Smell/Bug**: [AppPage.tsx](file:///c:/Users/HP/Downloads/sehri/pages/AppPage.tsx) extracts `selectedCity`, `selectedArea`, `selectedZone`, `onSelectCity`, etc. from [useSehri()](file:///c:/Users/HP/Downloads/sehri/context/SehriContext.tsx#171-178) and manually drills them down into `<FilterBar ...props />` as 10 different props.
**Risk**: This is textbook prop-drilling anti-pattern. Because [FilterBar](file:///c:/Users/HP/Downloads/sehri/components/FilterBar.tsx#22-219) is a heavy component, whenever *any* context value changes, [AppPage](file:///c:/Users/HP/Downloads/sehri/pages/AppPage.tsx#17-282) forces a full re-render of the prop tree. 
**Fix**: [FilterBar](file:///c:/Users/HP/Downloads/sehri/components/FilterBar.tsx#22-219) should just call [useSehri()](file:///c:/Users/HP/Downloads/sehri/context/SehriContext.tsx#171-178) internally to read/write its own slice of state, drastically simplifying [AppPage](file:///c:/Users/HP/Downloads/sehri/pages/AppPage.tsx#17-282) and React's diffing algorithm.

#### 3. Fragile Logic: Imperative DOM Manipulation (Hero.tsx)
**Smell/Bug**: Clicking the "Filters" button in the Hero triggers `document.getElementById('filters-section')?.scrollIntoView()`. 
**Risk**: Breaking React's declarative nature. If a developer accidentally renames that ID or if the ID hasn't mounted yet, the button silently fails.
**Fix**: Use a React `useRef` passed via context, or at least abstract the scroll logic into a stable utility function.

### Incremental Fix Plan (Batch 3)
- [ ] Add `useDeferredValue` to the search term in [Hero.tsx](file:///c:/Users/HP/Downloads/sehri/components/Hero.tsx) (or debounce the context push).
- [ ] Refactor [FilterBar.tsx](file:///c:/Users/HP/Downloads/sehri/components/FilterBar.tsx) to consume [useSehri()](file:///c:/Users/HP/Downloads/sehri/context/SehriContext.tsx#171-178) directly and remove the extreme prop drilling from [AppPage.tsx](file:///c:/Users/HP/Downloads/sehri/pages/AppPage.tsx).
- [ ] Add `useMemo` caching to the Leaflet Icons in [MapView](file:///c:/Users/HP/Downloads/sehri/components/MapView.tsx#87-199) to prevent DOM node recreation on every re-render.

