## Batch 2 Complete: Core Data State & Services

### Scope Inspected
- `src/context/SehriContext.tsx` (Global State)
- `src/services/spotService.ts` (API Integration)
- `src/hooks/useSpotFilter.ts` (Data Transformation)
- `src/utils/storage.ts` (Persistence)

### Findings & Risks

#### 1. Code Smell: Strict Mode Network Waterfall (SehriContext.tsx)
**Smell/Bug**: The `useEffect` that fetches [fetchSehriSpots()](file:///c:/Users/HP/Downloads/sehri/services/spotService.ts#27-62) has no cleanup/cancellation logic.
**Risk**: In React 18 Strict Mode (which we use in Dev), `useEffect` fires twice. Because there is no AbortController or mount check, the app makes *two* simultaneous network requests to Supabase on startup, wasting bandwidth and potentially causing race conditions when parsing the JSON payload.

#### 2. Performance: O(N) Inclusion Checks in Filter Loop (useSpotFilter.ts)
**Smell/Bug**: Inside the smart search logic, we construct a `smartCategories` array. Then, for *every single database item* (potentially thousands), we run `smartCategories.includes(item.venueType)`. 
**Risk**: `.includes()` on an array is an [O(N)](file:///c:/Users/HP/Downloads/sehri/components/FooterSEO.tsx#5-44) operation. Running an [O(N)](file:///c:/Users/HP/Downloads/sehri/components/FooterSEO.tsx#5-44) operation inside an [O(M)](file:///c:/Users/HP/Downloads/sehri/components/FooterSEO.tsx#5-44) filter loop creates an [O(N * M)](file:///c:/Users/HP/Downloads/sehri/components/FooterSEO.tsx#5-44) bottleneck. For large datasets, this will cause the UI to stutter while typing in the search bar. We should use a [Set](file:///c:/Users/HP/Downloads/sehri/context/LanguageContext.tsx#24-32) for [O(1)](file:///c:/Users/HP/Downloads/sehri/components/FooterSEO.tsx#5-44) lookups.

#### 3. Data Masking Bug: The "Empty DB" Fallback (spotService.ts)
**Smell/Bug**: When fetching from Supabase, if `data.length === 0`, the service forcibly returns local `SAMPLE_DATA`. 
**Risk**: If an Admin intentionally deletes all spots in the database, the frontend will ignore the live database state and suddenly show dummy text to the user. The fallback should only trigger on `error`, not on empty valid state.

### Incremental Fix Plan (Batch 2)
- [ ] Add an `isMounted` or `AbortController` flag to [loadData](file:///c:/Users/HP/Downloads/sehri/context/SehriContext.tsx#51-63) in [SehriContext.tsx](file:///c:/Users/HP/Downloads/sehri/context/SehriContext.tsx).
- [ ] Convert `smartCategories` array to `new Set()` inside [useSpotFilter.ts](file:///c:/Users/HP/Downloads/sehri/hooks/useSpotFilter.ts).
- [ ] Remove the `data.length === 0` fallback trigger from [spotService.ts](file:///c:/Users/HP/Downloads/sehri/services/spotService.ts).
